<!--
  ============================================================================
  reBot-DevArm_gripper.urdf
  ============================================================================
  Derived from the pristine SDK rigid "fixend" URDF (reBot-DevArm_fixend.urdf)
  by appending an actuated parallel-jaw gripper for Isaac Sim GRASP simulation.

  The arm chain (base_link .. link6 .. end_link) is COPIED VERBATIM from the
  fixend URDF — do not edit those numbers here; edit the pristine file and
  re-derive. Everything from the GRIPPER ADDITIONS marker onward is new and is
  approximated / documented in docs/sim/gripper_urdf_notes.md.

  Gripper model summary (REAL CAD-extracted articulation):
    - end_link <visual> = gripper_body.stl : the FIXED gripper body (housing +
      rail + rack/pinion), extracted from the assembly STEP in the end_link tool
      frame. Replaces the old fused end_link.STL (which baked body + retracted
      finger roots into one rigid mesh, 107x184x68 mm).
    - left_finger / right_finger : the real 01_Finger parts, articulated as two
      prismatic jaws (independent joints, coupled Isaac-side). Each finger mesh is
      authored in the tool frame; joints sit at the tool origin.
    - Per-finger travel 0 .. 0.0425 m  =>  clear jaw span 0.085 m (= the SDK
      "usable jaw limit", perception/ordinary_grasp.py:161). Verified with
      yourdfpy: closed gap ~0 mm, open clear gap 84.9 mm.
    - Envelope check: body + fingers reproduce the original end_link.STL Y/Z
      envelope EXACTLY (184.1 / 68.5 mm); X reaches 160.2 mm with the fingers
      fully modeled (the fused STL only showed 107 mm). Same gripper, articulated.

  TCP / frame convention (rebot_b601dm_kinematics.md §5, verified vs end_link.STL):
    approach = tool -X (body & fingers extend toward -X),
    jaw open/close = tool +-Y,  thickness = tool +-Z.
    tool = world + (100.1, 0, -195) mm, identity rotation.
  ============================================================================
-->
