  <!-- ==========================================================================
       GRIPPER ADDITIONS — REAL ARTICULATED PARALLEL-JAW (CAD-extracted)
       ==========================================================================
       The fingers below are the actual 01_Finger parts from the assembly STEP
       (reBot_B601_DM_v1.1_20260425.step), exported in the end_link tool frame via
       OCCT/XCAF. The fixed gripper body (housing + rail + rack/pinion) is the
       end_link <visual> above (gripper_body.stl). Together body + fingers reproduce
       the full physical gripper envelope (tool X[-0.160,0], Y[+-0.0925], Z[+-0.0347]),
       i.e. the SAME envelope as the original fused end_link.STL (107x184x68 mm) —
       just split into one fixed body + two moving fingers, not duplicated.

       Frame (docs/sim/assembly_mount_transforms.md, verified against end_link.STL):
         tool = world + (100.1, 0, -195) mm, identity rotation.
         approach axis = tool -X (gripper body & fingers extend toward -X).
         jaw open/close = tool +-Y.  thickness = tool +-Z.
       At the CAD pose the two fingers are nearly CLOSED (inner faces meet at Y~=0,
       outer edges at Y=+-31.4 mm). Each finger mesh is authored in the tool frame,
       so its prismatic joint origin is the tool origin (0,0,0) and the mesh carries
       its own tool-frame position.  Prismatic travel 0 -> 0.0425 m OPENS the jaw
       (left finger +Y, right finger -Y), giving a 0.085 m max span = SDK usable jaw
       limit (perception/ordinary_grasp.py:161).
  -->

  <!-- LEFT finger (+Y side). 01_Finger, tool-frame mesh.
       AABB (tool, m): X[-0.1603,-0.0953] Y[-0.0001,0.0314] Z[+-0.0197]. -->
  <link
    name="left_finger">
    <inertial>
      <!-- APPROX 0.03 kg 3D-printed blade. COM at mesh centroid (tool frame). -->
      <origin
